    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example utilizes a 6-speed manual gearbox delivering power to a GKN-Visco-Lok limited-slip differential. The chassis has been proactively addressed with rear subframe reinforcement plates to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The suspension geometry remains true, featuring a refreshed multi-link rear setup and MacPherson front struts for precise turn-in. While the exterior shows minor road wear, the mechanical vitals are robust, with consistent compression across all cylinders and a cooling system overhaul including a high-flow water pump. A mechanically sound driver\u2019s car optimized for longitudinal and lateral performance.",
